    • Enum Constant Detail

      • QUALITY_FRACTION

        public static final StatusConvention QUALITY_FRACTION
        The quality fraction status convention indicates a fractional quality of service, with zero representing complete failure and 1 representing completely successful operation. The method of computing this value is an algorithm that varies from device to device, and is explained in natural language in an unstructured text field in an electronic data sheet. Use Cases: Specify the quality of data produced by a star tracker.

      • BINARY_STATUS

        public static final StatusConvention BINARY_STATUS
        The binary status convention indicates whether a device is functioning correctly or erroneously. The data item has the value 0 if no error is being detected, and it has the value 1 if an error is present. Typically, the binary representation of such a variable would be bit or unsigned integer. Use Cases: The SOIS accelerometer interface uses this convention to report device status.

      • TERNARY_STATUS

        public static final StatusConvention TERNARY_STATUS
        The ternary status convention adds a warning state to the binary status. The three states follow: • OK – no error detected • Warning – action (such as restart) is not needed • Severe – action (such as restart) is needed Use Cases: Distinguish minor errors from major errors.
